By default the `bar.__next__()` method actually does exactly what you're looking for: https://github.com/WoLpH/python-progressbar/blob/develop/progressbar/bar.py#L430-L440

```python
    def __next__(self):
        try:
            value = next(self._iterable)
            if self.start_time is None:
                self.start()
            else:
                self.update(self.value + 1)
            return value
        except StopIteration:
            self.finish()
            raise
```

For Python 2 compatibility (and your convenience in this case) you can also use `bar.next()`

