A lightweight workaround for people running into this issue would be to subclass the resource for each route like this, which gives nice and predictable results:

```python
@api.route('/archive/<int:year>/')
class ArchiveYearResource(Resource):
    @api.marshal_with(archive)
    def get(self, year, month=-1, day=-1):
        """
        Returns list of blog posts from a specified time period.
        """
        return {'ret_year': year, 'ret_month': month, 'ret_day': day}

@api.route('/archive/<int:year>/<int:month>/')
class ArchiveMonthResource(ArchiveYearResource):
    pass

@api.route('/archive/<int:year>/<int:month>/<int:day>/')
class ArchiveDayResource(ArchiveYearResource):
    pass
```
